## Manual Trace — `nums = [-1, 0, 1, 2, -1, -4]`

After sorting: `[-4, -1, -1, 0, 1, 2]`

| i | nums[i] | left | right | total | Action |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 0 | -4 | 1 | 5 | -4+(-1)+2 = -3 | total < 0 → left++ |
| 0 | -4 | 2 | 5 | -4+(-1)+2 = -3 | total < 0 → left++ |
| 0 | -4 | 3 | 5 | -4+0+2 = -2 | total < 0 → left++ |
| 0 | -4 | 4 | 5 | -4+1+2 = -1 | total < 0 → left++ |
| 0 | -4 | 5 | 5 | left == right → exit while | |
| 1 | -1 | 2 | 5 | -1+(-1)+2 = 0 | **Found [-1,-1,2]** ✅, skip dupes |
| 1 | -1 | 3 | 4 | -1+0+1 = 0 | **Found [-1,0,1]** ✅, skip dupes |
| 2 | -1 | — | — | nums[2]==nums[1] → skip (duplicate i) | |
| 3 | 0 | 4 | 5 | 0+1+2 = 3 | total > 0 → right-- |
| 3 | 0 | 4 | 4 | left == right → exit | |

Result: `[[-1, -1, 2], [-1, 0, 1]]` ✅

